Standard Bank Seeks to Buy Banks in Nigeria, Angola, Times Says

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-07-03T09:43:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-03/standard-bank-seeks-to-buy-banks-in-nigeria-angola-times-says.html
Standard Bank Group Ltd. is seeking
to buy banks in  Nigeria  and  Angola  to expand its operations in
 Africa , the Sunday Times reported, citing Chief Executive
Officer Jacko Maree.  The lender is opening more branches in Nigeria and looking
at opportunities to buy banks there or in countries where it has
a smaller presence, Maree told the Johannesburg-based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nasreen Seria in Johannesburg at 
 nseria@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at   barden@bloomberg.net  